      "textOriginal": "I'm not a medical professional, but I pay attention to medical science regarding the virus, and I have common sense. Here's some food for thought regarding takeout: \n\nRegardless of our concerns about the health of the economy and keeping people in food service employed, let's be real. The virus sometimes lands inside storage, prepping, or delivery containers, on bowls, cooking tools, and the outside of food-handling gloves.\n\nYou know the expression \"I worked in a restaurant kitchen, so I don't eat food from one\"? I think a person is nuts if they have the option of carefully prepping the food themselves but choose not to do so for almost any reason. \n\nStaying and playing it's safe requires that you control whatever you can and hope for the best. These people are contaminating things and infecting others without knowing they are doing so. \n\nMany workers having mild symptoms and worry they have the virus, but without testing to confirm it they will not definitely lose their jobs. Some of these are food service people, and it is unreasonable to assume they being as careful as they need to be. \n\nThe danger with takeout food is real, and it goes beyond the packaging. The currently promoted suggestions for how to avoid the virus are not strong, prudent and effective enough. \n\nFor example, the virus can stay \"infectable\" for 3 hours while traveling in the air.. at whatever speed the air is moving. Six feet is only about how far a person can actively project the virus out you. However, yes, a person could have sneezed in a small room two hours ago and you can walk in and can get infected. \n\nThe bottom-line is that if you are absolutely taking a risk of food being contaminated with the virus. Cleaning the exterior of the packaging doesn't protect you any more than washing your skin gets the virus out from already inside you.\n\nControl what you can. Don't become a sad statistic. Don't take stupid risks. You won't die by ignore your craving for takeout. I'd rather be more tired than risk being on a ventilator like hundreds of thousands of people around the world were or are now.",

The N95 respirator mask with a valve, although very effective in preventing infection, does not filter the exhausted breath so it does not prevent transmission if you become infected. Moreover, both the N95 and surgical masks will trap the virus so that viral droplets are re-inhaled into the lungs of the victim where it could exponentially increase the viral load and severity of the infection yielding higher mortality rates. The N95 valve helps limit virus accumulation inside the mask so it should be altered to exhaust the contaminated breath into a filter “pillow” attached to the outside of the exhaust valve to capture the virus away from the inhalation portion of the mask. The exhaust filter can further protect the N95 filter from projectile droplets and reduce the potential for transmission to others or back to one’s own lungs. In the short term, you could add a surgical mask on top of your N95 valve or even add two cloth masks with a hole in the first one to allow breath vented from the valve to be trapped between the two surgical masks. Once you know you’re infected any fiber mask should be replaced regularly to reduce viral load available for inhalation. The better, and likely cheaper option in the long run, is the use of a true HAZMAT Level B full or half face respirator mask that has a disinfecting filter cartridge added over the exhaust valve to prevent viral transmission from the wearer. These masks have much better virus exclusion due to the silicone seal and use long lasting filter cartridges that are more effective than fiber masks and are safer to handle and dispose once contaminated. If a barbed hose bib were added to these masks, it would allow external attachment of an oxygen supply tube. Removal of an inflow filter cartridge would allow attachment of a ventilator hose. An everyman PPE kit should be composed of: two modified N95s w/exhaust filter, eye protection, gloves infused with antiviral solution, and a 2 oz. nebulizer with the antiviral solution to refresh the gloves. This kit would cost <$10 and wide distribution might be able to reduce the transmission rate sufficiently to eliminate the viral reservoir in the population. The Level B respirator modification is necessary to reduce the mortality rate in patients and to allow the medical staff to continue working safely, even if they get infected and are asymptomatic. I’m not a medical professional so please validate these suggestions with your respiratory therapist, especially if you succumb.",

      "textOriginal": "04/13/2020 21:36\n Already 28 corona dead in clinic\n Potsdam calls Bundeswehr for help (Does ventilation blow viruses in staff waiting room?)\n\n Brandenburg's second largest hospital no longer seems to be able to cope with the Corona situation in-house. Twenty-eight people have already died, reports the \"Potsdamer Neuesten Nachrichten\" (PNN), referring to a report by the Robert Koch Institute, which Mayor Mike Schubert is said to have only partially reproduced during a presentation last week.  The city of Potsdam has now even asked the Bundeswehr for help.  \"Supportive medical personnel are needed to deal with the outbreak events of the past few days,\" the newspaper quotes internal documents.\n\n According to the internal RKI report presented by the newspaper, there is a high probability that many patients would have contracted the Ernst von Bergmann clinic.  15 people currently need ventilation in the intensive care unit. Last Wednesday, a doctor from the clinic told ntv.de that the staff assumed that they would be infected.  According to the doctor, there is also an increased risk of infection in other hospitals.\n\n In the Klinkik in Potsdam, \"a large number of difficult courses requiring intensive care and ventilation\" can be expected in the coming weeks, the PNN cite the report of the institute.  The RKI had inspected the clinic on April 3.  According to the experts, the unusually strong outbreak could have been due to the fact that entire wards had moved and unidentified people could have spread the virus further.  Since the virus survives up to 72 hours on dead surfaces, this could also have been a source of infection in the house.\n\n Since the outbreak is not under control, according to the RKI report, consideration should be given to treating only corona patients in the house.  According to the newspaper, the house could become the Corona Clinic for all of Brandenburg.  Mayor Schubert withheld this information when presenting the report last week.  City of Potsdam has now informed the PNN that there are no plans of this kind.  The SPD mayor had called on the prosecutor to determine whether three doctors had failed to report.       "textDisplay": "Sorry, but you’ve got to be real. If somebody’s so large that they literally take up two seats, it is Definitely unfair to the other passengers sitting next to them, I should know because I fly a lot, and I’ve encountered this problem more times than I can count. I try my best to be polite as I possibly can because I don’t want to hurt their feelings, but truth be told, it drives me absolutely crazy when I’m squished up against a wall because the person beside me is literally three times my size and their ass is spilling out onto my seat. I’ve never been one to be politically correct, I say it like it is, and the fact is that morbidly obese people require a lot more space than the average size person, that’s not a personal attack, it’s not an insult, it’s a fact of life, why should my flight be absolutely ruined simply because the person next to me happens to be morbidly obese? Let’s call a spade a spade, if somebody is that large then they should require two seats, or option number two, the airlines themselves should be required to have seats they can accommodate larger passengers, because why should the cost be passed on to the consumer? Problem is no airline will ever do that because they only care about one thing, making as much money as they possibly can, overcrowding every single flight I’ve ever been on, and I’ve travelled all across the world, and frankly it doesn’t really matter what airline or how big the plane is, it’s the size of the passengers that can make or break the flight, and I’ve had some very uncomfortable rides. I’m just an average size guy, 5‘11“ tall and 165 pounds, the last time I flew nonstop from here in Toronto to Germany, I was sitting next to a man that must’ve been at least 500 pounds, and was a good 5 inches shorter than me, so throughout the entire flight, I was squished up against the window, because this man’s body was literally occupying Half of my seat. I got up, and politely ask the flight attendant if they had another seat available, and even though there were five empty seats in first class, they absolutely refused to move me. I told him I’d be more than happy to pay for a first class ticket just so I can spend my flight in comfort, yet they still refused, and I’ve been countered that with many different airlines, and I don’t know why they can’t fulfil a simple request to make their passengers comfortable if they have the extra space? I would never intentionally insult somebody just because of their size, we all come in different shapes and sizes, I believe it’s up to the carriers to provide adequate space for each person, because we’re not all 5‘5“ tall and 100 pounds! I remember coming home from that flight, I was in pain for three days afterwards because my legs had gone totally numb. My doctor told me that I could’ve got a blood clot in my legs under those circumstances even though I’m perfectly healthy, so what’s the answer? The person who requires more space can’t lose a few hundred pounds in two minutes, and there’s no way I’m going to start insulting a total stranger simply because they’re bigger than me, because face it, we’ve all been there at one point in our lives. I have Crohn’s disease, part of my treatment when I was younger was taking prednisone, which puts the weight on super fast, and I had ballooned up to 280 pounds in less than six months, and I had to go on a plane for a friends wedding. Again, that was probably one of the most uncomfortable flights I’ve ever had, only this time I was the heavy person. Thank God there were several empty seats on the plane, and this particular airline was quite polite and accommodating to the people sitting next to me and allow them to move, so that we could all fly with plenty of space, but even still I was in agony because I was just too big for the seat. I know everyone’s first instinct is to start insulting and berating the heavy set person, but I am not going to do that. Who the hell am I to judge? I think the bottom line is the airlines should be required by law to provide adequate seating for larger customers, they are hurting for money, and to give somebody a few extra inches on either side is not going to make them go broke, so why the hell don’t they just do it and shut up about it? And it is very true that over the years the seats have become closer and closer together, so they can squeeze as many people as they possibly can no matter how uncomfortable everybody is, perhaps it’s time we all stood up together as a society and told these airlines what we really think of them! I just take you guys, please do not start insulting somebody who is morbidly obese, because nobody wants to be that way usually, and you have no idea why they are that size, there could be 1 million different reasons, and most of them beyond the persons control, would you make fun of somebody because they have cancer? Of course not, so why is it OK to make fun of obesity, when it’s a disease like any other?",

       "videoId": "0CyIOWePQa8",
       "textDisplay": "I don't think your comment actually gives a better insight to the fashion industry than the interview does. I also don't think he meant fashion was cheap (not sure where you got that impression). I agree that there is always a hidden message in those ''serious'' interviews about fashion industry to imply its shallowness, which I don't want to judge here, as I simply enjoy fashion. But it's a whole another thing to say that this documentary conveys that Anna Wintour, or Alexander Wang, or the fashion industry is (or should be) cheap. More importantly, I also do not think your view about clothes made in China (or other non-Western places) is fair (or maybe just due to a lack of knowledge of this whole industry). Apart from some top brand (we are talking about Chanel, YSL here, and not their ''ready to wear'' collection) or some very small scale high fashion couture houses (if there are still any), for their technique and materials (only a few pieces are made by only a handful of people who can make them, wherever these people come from, mind you.) , all the well-known mass consumption fashion (brands like Michael Kors, Kate Spade, Maschino, Coach etc etc) are mostly made in China (a few are made in other countries, like Turkey, India, Vietnam, etc).       "textDisplay": "Let's remember that the \"mark of the beast\" represents the decision to follow the beast who opposes God and His laws. But who is the beast? Please ask God to give you light on this subject before continuing...\r\n\r\n----The beast is the same as the \"little horn\" described in Daniel 7:8. This little horn plucks up three of the other horns in order to set up his kingdom. This scene is describing a historical political event when the rulers of the earth were shifting power. The little horn represents Rome (more specifically, papal Rome) who overthrew the Heruli, Vandals, and Ostrogoths. Rome completed this conquest in 538 A.D.\r\n\r\n---\"And he shall speak great words against the most High, and shall wear out the saints of the most High, and think to change times and laws: and they shall be given into his hand until a time and times and the dividing of time.\" Daniel 7:25. The beast power speaks against God, persecutes God's people, and changes the laws of God. Papal Rome claims to serve God but they speak contrary to the word of God (this is the reason the protestant faith was born - to protest the false doctrines of the catholic church). During the dark ages (538 A.D. - 1798 A.D.), the papacy was responsible for the persecution and execution of millions of Christians. The changing of \"times and laws\" refers to the changes made to the ten commandments of God. In 321 A.D., Constantine declared Sunday (pagan day of worshipping the sun) would replace the seventh-day Sabbath as the new day of rest for all Christians, but God did not authorize any man to change His holy laws. The Catholic church maintains the sacredness of Sunday to this day.\r\n\r\n----\"Here is wisdom. Let him that hath understanding count the number of the beast: for it is the number of a man: and his number is Six hundred threescore and six.\" Revelation 13:18. \"VICARIUS FILII DEI\" are the Latin words found on the pope's crown. When you add these letters together using Latin numerals, the sum equals 666.\r\n\r\nSo what is the sign of allegiance to papal Rome? What is the sign of allegiance to God? \r\n\r\nThe mark of the beast will be received by all those who choose to worship on Sunday as opposed to the seventh-day Sabbath. It makes no difference which denomination you belong to. The simple matter at hand is this: will you choose to obey God rather than men?\r\n\r\nSome people argue that the mark of the beast is a micro chip. The micro chip is not the mark of the beast, however, it may play a very important role in forcing people to receive the mark of the beast. For example, the micro chip could be used as a tool to control the masses. We may hear such threats as \"worship on Sunday with us or we will turn off your micro chip and you will not be able to 'buy or sell.'\" (Revelation 13:7)\r\n\r\nWe are told that there will be \"wars, and rumours of wars,... and famines, and pestilences, and earthquakes, in divers places.\" (Matthew 24:6,7). As these calamities increase in scale and frequency, both politicians and the papacy will call upon the people to unite in solidarity in order to arrest the disasters and hatred which threatens the entire human race. How will people be asked to unite? By keeping Sunday as a day of rest. This proposal of Sunday rest is already found in the latest encyclical written by Pope Francis, and will be presented to world leaders for implementation in November 2017. \r\n\r\nSo what do we do? God instructs His people to keep His commandments (including the true seventh-day Sabbath). We are not to obey the laws of men over the laws of God. When it shall be declared BY LAW that Sunday is to be kept as a sacred day of rest, this is the time we are to \"flee into the mountains.\" \r\n\r\n----\"When ye therefore shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, stand in the holy place, (whoso readeth, let him understand:) Then let them which be in Judea flee into the mountains: Let him which is on the housetop not come down to take any thing out of his house: Neither let him which is in the field return back to take his clothes. And woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days! But pray ye that your flight be not in the winter neither on the sabbath day.\" Matthew 24:15-20\r\n\r\nPlease brethren, let no man fool you. If aliens come but \"speak not according to God's word,\" they are deceivers. Do not believe them.\r\n\r\nIf your pastor tells you not to worry about this day or that day, they \"speak not according to the word\" and are deceivers. Do not believe them.\r\n\r\nIf a bright and glorious figure unlike anything you have ever seen in your life claims to be Jesus and preforms many miracles and many wonders, and even causes fire to rain down from heaven... but he \"speaks not according to the word,\" he is a deceiver. Do not believe him (besides, Jesus said He would return in the clouds... not walk upon the earth as He did the first time He came). \r\n\r\nSatan is going to try many things to cause us to receive the mark of the beast (allegiance to the papacy via Sunday worship) because he knows that all who receive the mark of the beast will receive the wrath of God and will suffer the last 7 plagues found in Revelation chapter 16. Also, those who receive the mark of the beast will partake in the second death, which is eternal death (see Revelation 14:9-11).\r\n\r\nProbation for mankind finally closes when we make the decision to worship the beast (Sunday), or God (seventh-day Sabbath). All must make this final decision before Jesus returns. Remember, it is not \"thus saith tradition,\" or \"thus saith professor so-and-so,\" or \"thus saith pastor X,\" or \"thus saith my dead relatives...\" it is THUS SAITH THE LORD. \r\n\r\nWho will you worship?",

       "textDisplay": "THE NEW WORLD ORDER & THE MARK OF THE BEAST REVEALED!!!\n\nRevelation 14:9-14,  \"And the third angel followed them, saying with a loud voice, If any man worship the beast and his image, and receive his mark in his forehead, or in his hand, The same shall drink of the wine of the wrath of God, which is poured out without mixture into the cup of his indignation; and he shall be tormented with fire and brimstone in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb: And the smoke of their torment ascendeth up for ever and ever: and they have no rest day nor night, who worship the beast and his image, and whosoever receiveth the mark of his name. Here is the patience of the saints: here are they that keep the commandments of God, and the faith of Jesus.\"\n\nThe\"Mark of the Beast\" is about worship!!! Anyone who will not worship the beast/antichrist will be removed from economic participation and ultimately die when the \"Mark\" will be enforced.\n\nRevelation 13:16-18 -And he (Antichrist) causeth all, both small and great, rich and poor, free and bond, to receive a mark in their right hand, or in their foreheads: And that no man might buy or sell, save he that had the mark, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name. Here is wisdom. Let him that hath understanding count the number of the beast: for it is the number of a man; and his number is Six hundred threescore and six.  \n\nThe widespread idea that the mark is visible is false. The computerchip is a hoax that has set up the world to receive the true mark.  Satan is wiser than man. A visible mark which the world has been taught, this would deceive no one. The mark is given to those who will continue to sin and transgress God's holy law, while the saints of God will receive His seal because they walked not after the flesh, but after the Spirit. They would refuse to yield up temptation to sin against God. \nThe works of true love will bring forth the works of the law, which will be established in the true Christian, which is the character that Christ is truly abiding. The old self will die which loved the life of sin and pleasure. The old man will be crucified and will become a new creature. Then they will truly be born again. Repentance has always be the message to the world after the fall of Adam and Eve. \n\nIn Bible prophecy the forehead represents our mind where we make the free will choice to serve God in obedience to His law or to serve Satan in sin, which is transgression of that law.  1John 3:4.\n In Bible prophecy the hand represents us being forced against our will or being led captive for not obeying. So if we do not worship the beast and his image by choosing to disobey and serve God,  the Antichrist will then try and force us against our will to worship him or have no ability to buy and sell. Then they will behead (Revelation 20:4) all who would not bow to this false worship system, which is being set up as we speak by the Antichrist. The world is being groomed already to receive the mark of the beast and thus,  refuse to receive the seal of God. If we are being sealed by the Holy Spirit,  we will have corresponding works of the law that Jesus is writing in the mind and heart of the true believer. \n\nSo. What is the mark of the beast/antichrist?\n\nThe Roman Catholic Church says:\n\n\"Sunday is our 'MARK' or authority. . .the church is above the Bible, and this transference of Sabbath observance is proof of that fact\" Catholic Record of London, Ontario Sept 1,1923.\n\nThe Mark of the Beast—When Sunday observance shall be enforced by law, and the world shall be enlightened concerning the obligation of the true Sabbath, then whoever shall transgress the command of God, to obey a precept which has no higher authority than that of Rome, will thereby honor popery above God. He is paying homage to Rome, and to the power which enforces the institution ordained by Rome. He is worshiping the beast and his image. As men then reject the institution which God has declared to be the sign of His authority, and honor in its stead that which Rome has chosen as the token of her supremacy, they will thereby accept the sign of allegiance to Rome,—“the mark of the beast.” And it is not until the issue is thus plainly set before the people, and they are brought to choose between the commandments of God and the commandments of men, that those who continue in transgression will receive “the mark of the beast.” Revelation 14: 9-12.\n\n\"The Bible says, Remember that thou keep holy the Sabbath day. The Catholic church says, No! By my divine power I abolish the Sabbath day, and command you to keep the first day of the week. And lo, the entire civilized world bows down in reverent obedience to the command of the holy Catholic church!\" Father Enright, C.S.S.R. of the RedemptoralCollege, Kansas City, History of the Sabbath, p. 802\n\nNo one has yet received the mark of the beast. The testing time has not yet come. There are true Christians in every church, not excepting the Roman Catholic communion. None are condemned until they have had the light and have seen the obligation of the fourth commandment. But when the decree shall go forth enforcing the counterfeit sabbath, and the loud cry of the third angel shall warn men against the worship of the beast and his image, the line will be clearly drawn between the false and the true. Then those who still continue in transgression will receive the mark of the beast.\n\nWhen Seal of God Is Refused—If the light of truth has been presented to you, revealing the Sabbath of the fourth commandment, and showing that there is no foundation in the Word of God for Sunday observance, and yet you still cling to the false sabbath, refusing to keep holy the Sabbath which God calls “My holy day,” you receive the mark of the beast. When does this take place? When you obey the decree that commands you to cease from labor on Sunday and worship God, while you know that there is not a word in the Bible showing Sunday to be other than a common working day, you consent to receive the mark of the beast, and refuse the seal of God.\n\nAs a Result of Disregard of Light—God has given men the Sabbath as a sign between Him and them, as a test of their loyalty.        "textDisplay": "@Edward The Booble I learned that the terms “agnostic” and “agnosticism” were famously coined in the late nineteenth century by the English biologist, T.H. Huxley. He said that he originally invented the word “Agnostic” to denote people who, like [himself], confess themselves to be hopelessly ignorant concerning a variety of matters, about which metaphysicians and theologians, both orthodox and heterodox, dogmatise with the utmost confidence. (1884)\n\nincluding of course the matter of God’s existence. He did not, however, define “agnosticism” simply as the state of being an agnostic. Instead, he often used that term to refer to a normative epistemological principle, something similar to (though weaker than) what we now call “evidentialism”. Roughly, Huxley’s principle says that it is wrong to say that one knows or believes that a proposition is true without logically satisfactory evidence (Huxley 1884 and 1889). But it was Huxley’s application of this principle to theistic and atheistic belief that ultimately had the greatest influence on the meaning of the term. He argued that, since neither of those beliefs is adequately supported by evidence, we ought to suspend judgment on the issue of whether or not there is a God.\nNowadays, the term “agnostic” is often used (when the issue is God’s existence) to refer to those who follow the recommendation expressed in the conclusion of Huxley’s argument: an agnostic is a person who has entertained the proposition that there is a God but believes neither that it is true nor that it is false. Not surprisingly, then, the term “agnosticism” is often defined, both in and outside of philosophy, not as a principle or any other sort of proposition but instead as the psychological state of being an agnostic. Call this the “psychological” sense of the term. It is certainly useful to have a term to refer to people who are neither theists nor atheists, but philosophers might wish that some other term besides “agnostic” (“theological skeptic”, perhaps?) were used. The problem is that it is also very useful for philosophical purposes to have a name for the epistemological position that follows from the premise of Huxley’s argument, the position that neither theism nor atheism is known, or most ambitiously, that neither the belief that God exists nor the belief that God does not exist has positive epistemic status of any sort. Just as the metaphysical question of God’s existence is central to philosophy of religion, so too is the epistemological question of whether or not theism or atheism is known or has some other sort of positive epistemic status. And given the etymology of “agnostic”, what better term could there be for a negative answer to that epistemological question than “agnosticism”? Further, as suggested earlier, it is, for very good reason, typical in philosophy to use the suffix “-ism” to refer to a proposition instead of to a state or condition, since only the former can sensibly be tested by argument.\nIf, however, “agnosticism” is defined as a proposition, then “agnostic” must be defined in terms of “agnosticism” instead of the other way around. Specifically, “agnostic” must be defined as a person who believes that the proposition “agnosticism” is true instead of “agnosticism” being defined as the state of being an agnostic. And if the proposition in question is that neither theism nor atheism is known to be true, then the term “agnostic” can no longer serve as a label for those who are neither theists nor atheists since one can consistently believe that atheism (or theism) is true while denying that atheism (or theism) is known to be true.\nWhen used in this epistemological sense, the term “agnosticism” can very naturally be extended beyond the issue of what is or can be known to cover a large family of positions, depending on what sort of “positive epistemic status” is at issue. For example, it might be identified with any of the following positions: that neither theistic belief nor atheistic belief is justified, that neither theistic belief nor atheistic belief is rationally required, that neither belief is rationally permissible, that neither has warrant, that neither is reasonable, or that neither is probable. Also, in order to avoid the vexed issue of the nature of knowledge, one can simply distinguish as distinct members of the “agnosticism family” each of the following claims about intellectually sophisticated people: (i) neither theism nor atheism is adequately supported by the internal states of such people, (ii) neither theistic belief nor atheistic belief coheres with the rest of their beliefs, (iii) neither theistic nor atheistic belief results from reliable belief-producing processes, (iv) neither theistic belief nor atheistic belief results from faculties aimed at truth that are functioning properly in an appropriate environment, and so on.\nNotice too that, even if agnosticism were defined as the rather extreme position that neither theistic belief nor atheistic belief ever has positive epistemic status of any sort, it wouldn’t follow by definition that no agnostic is either a theist or an atheist. Some fideists, for example, believe that neither atheistic belief nor theistic belief is supported or sanctioned in any way at all by reason because reason leaves the matter of God’s existence completely unresolved. Yet they have faith that God exists and such faith (at least in some cases) involves belief. Thus, some fideists are extreme agnostics in the epistemological sense even though they are not agnostics in the psychological sense.\nIt is also worth mentioning that, even in Huxley’s time, some apophatic theists embraced the term “agnostic”, claiming that all good Christians worshipped an “unknown God”. More recently, some atheists proudly call themselves “agnostic atheists”, although with further reflection the symmetry between this position and fideism might give them pause. More likely, though, what is being claimed by these self-identified agnostic atheists is that, while their belief that God does not exist has positive epistemic status of some sort (minimally, it is not irrational), it does not have the sort of positive epistemic status that can turn true belief into knowledge.\nNo doubt both senses of “agnosticism”, the psychological and the epistemological, will continue to be used both inside and outside of philosophy. Hopefully, context will help to disambiguate. In the remainder of this entry, however, the term “agnosticism” will be used in its epistemological sense. This makes a huge difference to the issue of justification. Consider, for example, this passage written by the agnostic, Anthony Kenny (1983: 84–85):\n\nI do not myself know of any argument for the existence of God which I find convincing; in all of them I think I can find flaws. Equally, I do not know of any argument against the existence of God which is totally convincing; in the arguments I know against the existence of God I can equally find flaws. So that my own position on the existence of God is agnostic.\n\nIt is one thing to ask whether Kenny’s inability to find arguments that convince him of God’s existence or non-existence justifies him personally in suspending judgment about the existence of God. It is quite another to ask whether this inability (or anything else) would justify his believing that no one (or at least no one who is sufficiently intelligent and well-informed) has a justified belief about God’s existence.\nIf agnosticism (in one sense of the word) is the position that neither theism nor atheism is known, then it might be useful to use the term “gnosticism” to refer to the contradictory of that position, that is, to the position that either theism or atheism is known. That view would, of course, come in two flavors: theistic gnosticism—the view that theism is known (and hence atheism is not)—and atheistic gnosticism—the view that atheism is known (and hence theism is not).",

I live in Illinois, which is thankfully one of the states in the union which is pretty good on LGBT protections.\n\nThere are plenty of states which are not.\n\nDoes my access to gay marriage prior to the Supreme Court’s intervention in 2015 negate the fact that there were people in other states who lacked it? Short answer: no.\n\nThose are the people I’m really advocating for here. I’m advocating for myself too, of course, but I guarantee you all of those states have LGBT populations whose rights are being restricted in ways that their straight counterparts are not solely based on their sexual orientation and/or gender identity.\n\nAnd finally, 3a. On the subject of dissenting opinions, when peoples’ opinions are uninformed, ignorant, and/or rooted in bigotry and seek to strip other people of their rights, rights which these people have always enjoyed because every citizen is supposed to have them, then it’s a little more serious than just a “dissenting opinion.” You are welcome to dissent all you want, sure, but don’t tell me to just accept it and get over it.
